 Hi David,

  Good morning,

  Following our discussion, I have evaluated two approaches for setting up the D_RAWCDC database with SADB and AWS schemas.

  Note: The DB RENAME option we discussed earlier won't work here since we are only migrating two schemas (SADB & AWS), not the entire D_BRONZE database.

  Option 1: Schema Clone

  ┌───────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Pros                  │ Cons                             │
  ├───────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Data preserved as-is  │ Grants do NOT transfer           │
  ├───────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Quick clone operation │ Need to re-grant all permissions │
  ├───────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Easy rollback         │ Streams need recreation          │
  └───────────────────────┴──────────────────────────────────┘

  Option 2: Fresh Setup + Reload

  ┌───────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────┐
  │ Pros                          │ Cons                      │
  ├───────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────┤
  │ Clean start                   │ Requires data reload      │
  ├───────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────┤
  │ Simple IDMC connection update │ Takes more time initially │
  ├───────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────┤
  │ No grant migration complexity │                           │
  └───────────────────────────────┴───────────────────────────┘

  Quick Comparison

  ┌────────────┬───────────────┬────────────────────┐
  │ Criteria   │ Clone         │ Fresh Setup        │
  ├────────────┼───────────────┼────────────────────┤
  │ Complexity │ Higher        │ Lower              │
  ├────────────┼───────────────┼────────────────────┤
  │ Grants     │ Need re-grant │ Setup from scratch │
  ├────────────┼───────────────┼────────────────────┤
  │ Best for   │ Production    │ Development        │
  └────────────┴───────────────┴────────────────────┘

  My Suggestion: Since we are still in the development stage and will need to reload data anyway after updating the IDMC connection details, I would suggest Option 2 (Fresh Setup). It gives us a clean start without carrying over any legacy
  configurations.

  Action required:

  • Create D_RAWCDC database with SADB and AWS schemas
  • Update IDMC connection to target D_RAWCDC
  • Reload the data

  Please let me know your thoughts.

 Option A (Conversational)

  Since we're in early development and data reload is expected anyway once IDMC connection changes, I'd go with Option 2. Cleaner approach, no baggage from old setup.

  Next steps would be:

  • Clear existing SADB and AWS objects from D_BRONZE
  • Create D_RAWCDC with SADB and AWS schemas
  • Point IDMC to the new DB
  • Reload data

  ────────────────────────────────────────

  Option B (Direct)

  My recommendation is Option 2. We're still in development, and IDMC connection update will require data reload regardless. Makes sense to start fresh.

  To proceed:

  • Drop existing SADB & AWS schemas from D_BRONZE
  • Setup D_RAWCDC database (SADB & AWS schemas)
  • Update IDMC target connection
  • Trigger data reload

  ────────────────────────────────────────

  Option C (Brief)

  Given we're in dev stage and reload is inevitable after connection change, Option 2 makes more sense. Fresh setup, no complications.

  Actions:

  • Cleanup SADB & AWS in D_BRONZE
  • New DB & schemas creation
  • IDMC connection update
  • Data reload


  Regards,
  Babu
